Pre-Game Insights: The Nats are deep underdogs today, at +160 to win on the moneyline.
Manager Dave Martinez said that he would like to seed Trevor Williams back into the rotation on Friday against the Cubs.
Luis Garcia Jr. at a WAR of +2.9, and Jacob Young at +2.7 lead the Nats on the FanGraphs' WAR leaderboard.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game is the series finale for the Washington Nationals with the Mets.
The Nationals need to go 4-7 or better to beat their 2023 win total.
The Nats starting pitchers have a combined ERA of 4.37 and 21st in MLB.
